  "text": "The percentage body weight gain of the group of animals treated with UF-MOS was lower than MCF-MORS (7.5%, 15%, 22.5% and 30%) and the control (Table 6 ). This study explains that the body weight may depend on PCV amounts, erythrocyte counts, and immune systems. Our opinion corroborates the former result which reported that body weight and leukocyte counts were significantly (p < 0.05) lowered in the anemic piglets than the normal group [CITATION_1] . Also, the blood quantity and quality of packed cell volume (PCV) were significantly (p < 0.05) elevated in animals fed with MCF-MORS when compared to UF-MOS group (Figure 1 ).",
